		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Kreese wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">This is really cool! Is there any good Blue-tooth controllers for iPhone?</div><br /><br />It works with all iCade-compatible controllers which includes the <a href="http://www.icontrolpad.com" class="postlink">iControlPad</a> and the entire <a href="http://www.ionaudio.com/products/gaming/ipad-gaming" class="postlink">iCade family</a>. I have an iCade for my iPad and am rather impressed with the quality of the controls. Here's a <a href="http://youtu.be/stnsDGgIMk4" class="postlink">video of me playing BK2 on it.</a><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Kreese wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Anyway, great idea to release this game this way as an option. I suppose Sivak will get his share of every copy that will be sold?</div><br /><br />At the moment I'm only publishing the freely-available demo of BK2. Whether or not the full game will see a release apart from the cartridge version is up to Sivak and bunnyboy.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
