		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I tried the new iPhone version on lecture break today, and here are a couple of things I noticed:<br /><br />- At one point the Left button on the &quot;d-pad&quot; got stuck. Sorry, but I have no idea how to reproduce this.<br />- In landscape mode clicking on top of the screen takes you to retrousb.com, even though there's no visible link. I tried couple of times to open the notifications bar or whatever it's called (you know, by sliding downwards at the top of the screen), and it would open up the link instead. Also when I returned to the game again, it would sometimes re-open the page instantaneously even when I didn't touch anything.<br />- Sometimes the controls didn't seem to work after re-opening the game. Once again, no idea how to reproduce this, but I'll let you know if it keeps on occurring again.<br />- Would be nice to have an option to turn the sound off. Also would be nice if it allowed the music player to be used while playing the game.

		

		</td>
